<paragraph blockId="18.[108,636,1466,1729]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">
IDENTIFICATION: Descriptions and measurements of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1913" box="[211,417,1671,1695]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Lionycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spurrelli">
<emphasis box="[211,417,1671,1695]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">Lionycteris spurrelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Phillips, C. J." box="[149,318,1705,1729]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 138" refId="ref41317" refString="Phillips, C. J. 1971. The dentition of glossophagine bats: development, morphological chractreristics, variation, pathology, and evolution. University of Kansas Museum of Natural History Miscellaneous Publications 64: 1 - 138." type="journal article" year="1971">Phillips (1971)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Carter, D. C. &amp; P. G. Dolan" box="[338,632,1705,1729]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 136" refId="ref33829" refString="Carter, D. C., and P. G. Dolan. 1978. Catalogue of type specimens of Neotropical bats in selected European museums. Special Publication of the Museum of Texas Tech University 15: 1 - 136." type="journal article" year="1978">Carter and Dolan (1978)</bibRefCitation>
,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[684,1213,1089,1728]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">
<bibRefCitation author="Swanepoel, P. &amp; H. H. Genoways" box="[684,1051,1089,1113]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="1 - 441" refId="ref42730" refString="Swanepoel, P., and H. H. Genoways. 1979. Morphometrics. In R. J. Baker, J. K. Jones, Jr., and D. C. Carter (editors), Biology of bats of the New World family Phyllostomatidae, Part III: 1 - 441. Special Publications, Texas Tech University Museum 16." type="journal article" year="1979">Swanepoel and Genoways (1979)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, S. L. &amp; H. H. Genoways" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="213 - 236" refId="ref44459" refString="Williams, S. L., and H. H. Genoways. 1980. Results of the ALCOA Foundation-Suriname expeditions. II. Additional records of bats (Mammalia: Chiroptera) from Suriname. Annals of Carnegie Museum 49: 213 - 236." type="journal article" year="1980">Williams and Genoways (1980)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Koopman, K. F." box="[884,1069,1123,1147]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" refId="ref37857" refString="Koopman, K. F. 1993. Order Chiroptera. Mammal species of the world: a taxonomic and geographic reference, 2 nd ed.: 137 - 241. Washington: Smithsonian Institution Press." type="book" year="1993">Koopman (1993)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Zortea, M. &amp; R. Gregorin &amp; A. D. Ditchfield" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="95 - 96" refId="ref44813" refString="Zortea, M., R. Gregorin, and A. D. Ditchfield. 1998. Lichonycteris obscura from Espirito Santo state, southeastern Brazil. Chiroptera Neotropical 4: 95 - 96." type="journal article" year="1998">Zortéa et al. (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gregorin, R. &amp; A. D. Ditchfield" box="[763,1089,1157,1181]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="403 - 414" refId="ref36652" refString="Gregorin, R., and A. D. Ditchfield. 2005. New genus and species of nectar-feeding bat in the tribe Lonchophyllini (Phyllostomidae: Glossophaginae) from northeastern Brazil. Journal of Mammalogy 86: 403 - 414." type="journal article" year="2005">Gregorin and Ditchfield (2005)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Woodman, N. &amp; R. M. Timm" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="437 - 476" refId="ref44759" refString="Woodman, N., and R. M. Timm. 2006. Characters and phylogenetic relationships of nectar-feeding bats, with descriptions of new Lonchophylla from western South America (Mammalia: Chiroptera: Phyllostomidae: Lonchophyllini). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 119: 437 - 476." type="journal article" year="2006">Woodman and Timm (2006)</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Woodman, N." box="[927,1117,1192,1216]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="340 - 358" refId="ref44716" refString="Woodman, N. 2007. A new species of nectar-feeding bat, genus Lonchophylla, from western Colombia and western Ecuador (Mammalia: Chiroptera: Phyllostomidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 120: 340 - 358." type="journal article" year="2007">Woodman (2007)</bibRefCitation>
. No subspecies are currently recognized in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Griffiths and Gardner, 2008 b)" baseAuthorityName="Griffiths and Gardner" baseAuthorityYear="2008" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Lionycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spurrelli">
<emphasis box="[1092,1212,1226,1250]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">L. spurrelli</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Griffiths, T. A. &amp; A. L. Gardner" box="[691,1024,1260,1284]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="244 - 255" refId="ref36809" refString="Griffiths, T. A., and A. L. Gardner. 2008 b (&quot; 2007 &quot;). Subfamily Lonchophyllinae Griffiths, 1982. In A. L. Gardner (editor), Mammals of South America, vol. 1: Marsupials, xenarthrans, shrews, and bats: 244 - 255. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2008">Griffiths and Gardner, 2008b</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Our specimens conform in all respects with previous descriptions of this species and exhibit the diagnostic characteristics of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Griffiths and Gardner" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[776,892,1362,1386]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Lionycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spurrelli">
<emphasis box="[776,892,1362,1386]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">L. spurrelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: base of dorsal pelage darker than tips; GLS &lt;
<quantity box="[875,959,1397,1421]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" unit="mm" value="21.0">21 mm</quantity>
; rostrum shorter than braincase; upper premolars not conspicuously elongated; well-developed lingual cusps present on both upper premolars; p4 and p5 short and broad; and main cusps of p4 and p5 high and narrow (
<bibRefCitation author="Woodman, N. &amp; R. M. Timm" box="[691,994,1567,1591]" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="437 - 476" refId="ref44759" refString="Woodman, N., and R. M. Timm. 2006. Characters and phylogenetic relationships of nectar-feeding bats, with descriptions of new Lonchophylla from western South America (Mammalia: Chiroptera: Phyllostomidae: Lonchophyllini). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington 119: 437 - 476." type="journal article" year="2006">Woodman and Timm, 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Griffiths, T. A. &amp; A. L. Gardner" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" pagination="244 - 255" refId="ref36809" refString="Griffiths, T. A., and A. L. Gardner. 2008 b (&quot; 2007 &quot;). Subfamily Lonchophyllinae Griffiths, 1982. In A. L. Gardner (editor), Mammals of South America, vol. 1: Marsupials, xenarthrans, shrews, and bats: 244 - 255. Chicago: University of Chicago Press." type="book chapter" year="2008">Griffiths and Gardner, 2008b</bibRefCitation>
). Our vouchers fall within the range of measurements reported for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Griffiths and Gardner" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[979,1090,1635,1659]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Lionycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="18" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="spurrelli">
<emphasis box="[979,1090,1635,1659]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="18">L. spurrelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
